    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring a factory-spec 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This unit maintains flawless compression across all rotor faces, with a seamless transition through the secondary turbocharger at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains structurally original, benefiting from the Type R double-wishbone suspension geometry and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line in the complex solenoid rack has been meticulously inspected, ensuring zero boost leaks. The exterior retains its factory finish with no signs of oxidation, while the cockpit features pristine, wear-free plastics and original instrumentation. A true driver\u2019s machine preserved in its peak mechanical state.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
